{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372681809,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_q7gSUWYeKwEy76ZSZNyucYTm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","offset":289,"limit":172},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n289: This is the single machine-readable projection of the prose Intent Model (§2) and the per-surface maps (§4 Webflow, §5 Motion.dev, §6 OpenCode). The prose sections above are the human-facing contract; this block is the byte-for-byte source a deterministic router-replay parses. Keep the two in sync: when a map row changes above, update the matching `RESOURCE_MAP` entry here.\n290: \n291: A drift guard (`.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`) keeps this block honest: it fails if any path here is missing on disk, if any routable `references/`/`assets/` doc stops being covered, or if an explicit full path named in the prose maps is absent here. Run it standalone with `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` from `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts`.\n292: \n293: This projection is intentionally lossy in two documented ways the flat dictionary cannot express, both enforced by the prose contract and the surface-detection pseudocode in `SKILL.md` §2:\n294: \n295: - **No phase boosts.** The `+5` unambiguous-phase boost from the §2 scoring algorithm is not represented; every keyword carries unit weight here.\n296: - **No doc-only anti-signals.** The `sk-code -2 / sk-doc +3` anti-signals (§2) that route prose-only edits away from this skill are a pre-filter the flat model does not carry.\n297: \n298: ```python\n299: # Always-loaded routing preamble: every code task detects stack, detects phase,\n300: # consults the router, and applies the universal quality baseline before any\n301: # surface-specific resource. These are loaded on every route.\n302: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = [\n303:     \"references/stack_detection.md\",\n304:     \"references/phase_detection.md\",\n305:     \"references/smart_routing.md\",\n306:     \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n307: ]\n308: \n309: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n310:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\":     {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"create\", \"feature\", \"component\", \"module\", \"authoring\"]},\n311:     \"CODE_QUALITY\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lint\", \"format\", \"quality gate\", \"naming\", \"standards\", \"code smell\"]},\n312:     \"DEBUGGING\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"debug\", \"broken\", \"failing\", \"stack trace\", \"console error\", \"regression\"]},\n313:     \"VERIFICATION\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"verify\", \"passing\", \"type-check\", \"alignment drift\", \"completion claim\"]},\n314:     \"TESTING\":            {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"unit test\", \"integration test\", \"coverage\", \"vitest\", \"pytest\", \"shellcheck\"]},\n315:     \"DEPLOYMENT\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"deploy\", \"cdn\", \"wrangler\", \"minify\", \"staging\", \"production release\"]},\n316:     \"PERFORMANCE\":        {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lighthouse\", \"core web vitals\", \"largest contentful\", \"pagespeed\", \"jank\", \"frame budget\"]},\n317:     \"ANIMATION\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"transition\", \"gsap\", \"lenis\", \"carousel\", \"parallax\"]},\n318:     \"MOTION_DEV\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"motion.dev\", \"motion-dev\", \"animate()\", \"inview\", \"scroll()\", \"cross-stack animation\"]},\n319:     \"FORMS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"form upload\", \"filepond\", \"field validation\", \"focus trap\"]},\n320:     \"VIDEO\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"hls\", \"adaptive stream\", \"video player\"]},\n321:     \"HOOKS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"session-prime\", \"user-prompt-submit\", \"pre-tool-use\", \"post-tool-use\"]},\n322:     \"CONFIG\":             {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"jsonc\", \".json\", \".jsonc\", \"descriptor\", \"config schema\"]},\n323:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"typescript\", \".ts\", \".tsx\", \"python\", \".py\", \"shell script\", \"bash\", \".sh\", \"commonjs\", \".cjs\", \".mjs\", \"docstring\"]},\n324: }\n325: \n326: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n327:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\": [\n328:         \"references/universal/multi_agent_research.md\",\n329:         \"references/webflow/implementation/implementation_workflows.md\",\n330:         \"references/webflow/implementation/async_patterns.md\",\n331:         \"references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md\",\n332:         \"references/webflow/implementation/security_patterns.md\",\n333:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\",\n334:         \"references/webflow/implementation/webflow_patterns.md\",\n335:         \"references/webflow/shared/dev_workflow.md\",\n336:         \"references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md\",\n337:         \"references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md\",\n338:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/agent_authoring.md\",\n339:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/command_authoring.md\",\n340:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/skill_authoring.md\",\n341:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/mcp_server_authoring.md\",\n342:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/spec_folder_authoring.md\",\n343:         \"assets/opencode/recipes/spec_folder_write.md\",\n344:         \"assets/universal/patterns/README.md\",\n345:         \"assets/webflow/integrations/README.md\",\n346:         \"assets/webflow/patterns/README.md\",\n347:         \"assets/webflow/templates/README.md\"\n348:     ],\n349:     \"CODE_QUALITY\": [\n350:         \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n351:         \"references/universal/code_style_guide.md\",\n352:         \"references/webflow/shared/cross_language_rules.md\",\n353:         \"references/webflow/shared/enforcement.md\",\n354:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md\",\n355:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/javascript_checklist.md\",\n356:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md\",\n357:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/python_checklist.md\",\n358:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/shell_checklist.md\",\n359:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md\"\n360:     ],\n361:     \"DEBUGGING\": [\n362:         \"references/universal/error_recovery.md\",\n363:         \"references/webflow/debugging/debugging_workflows.md\",\n364:         \"references/webflow/debugging/error_recovery.md\",\n365:         \"assets/universal/checklists/debugging_checklist.md\",\n366:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/debugging_checklist.md\"\n367:     ],\n368:     \"VERIFICATION\": [\n369:         \"references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md\",\n370:         \"references/opencode/shared/alignment_verification_automation.md\",\n371:         \"assets/universal/checklists/verification_checklist.md\",\n372:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/verification_checklist.md\",\n373:         \"assets/scripts/README.md\"\n374:     ],\n375:     \"TESTING\": [\n376:         \"assets/motion_dev/playbook_entries.md\"\n377:     ],\n378:     \"DEPLOYMENT\": [\n379:         \"references/webflow/deployment/cdn_deployment.md\",\n380:         \"references/webflow/deployment/minification_guide.md\",\n381:         \"references/webflow/deployment/webflow_staging_production.md\",\n382:         \"assets/webflow/scripts/README.md\"\n383:     ],\n384:     \"PERFORMANCE\": [\n385:         \"references/webflow/performance/cwv_remediation.md\",\n386:         \"references/webflow/performance/interaction_gated_loading.md\",\n387:         \"references/webflow/performance/resource_loading.md\",\n388:         \"references/webflow/performance/third_party.md\",\n389:         \"references/webflow/performance/webflow_constraints.md\",\n390:         \"references/webflow/verification/performance_checklist.md\",\n391:         \"references/webflow/implementation/performance_patterns.md\",\n392:         \"references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md\",\n393:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/performance_loading_checklist.md\"\n394:     ],\n395:     \"ANIMATION\": [\n396:         \"references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md\",\n397:         \"references/webflow/implementation/swiper_patterns.md\"\n398:     ],\n399:     \"MOTION_DEV\": [\n400:         \"references/motion_dev/quick_start.md\",\n401:         \"references/motion_dev/animate_and_timelines.md\",\n402:         \"references/motion_dev/scroll_and_gestures.md\",\n403:         \"references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md\",\n404:         \"references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md\",\n405:         \"assets/motion_dev/install_card.md\",\n406:         \"assets/motion_dev/snippets/README.md\"\n407:     ],\n408:     \"FORMS\": [\n409:         \"references/webflow/implementation/form_upload_workflows.md\",\n410:         \"references/webflow/implementation/focus_management.md\"\n411:     ],\n412:     \"VIDEO\": [\n413:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\"\n414:     ],\n415:     \"HOOKS\": [\n416:         \"references/opencode/shared/hooks.md\"\n417:     ],\n418:     \"CONFIG\": [\n419:         \"references/opencode/config/style_guide.md\",\n420:         \"references/opencode/config/quality_standards.md\",\n421:         \"references/opencode/config/quick_reference.md\",\n422:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/config_checklist.md\"\n423:     ],\n424:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": [\n425:         \"references/webflow/css/style_guide.md\",\n426:         \"references/webflow/css/quality_standards.md\",\n427:         \"references/webflow/css/quick_reference.md\",\n428:         \"references/webflow/css/patterns.md\",\n429:         \"references/webflow/html/style_guide.md\",\n430:         \"references/webflow/html/quality_standards.md\",\n431:         \"references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n432:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n433:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n434:         \"references/opencode/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n435:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n436:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n437:         \"references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md\",\n438:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md\",\n439:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md\",\n440:         \"references/opencode/python/style_guide.md\",\n441:         \"references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md\",\n442:         \"references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md\",\n443:         \"references/opencode/shell/style_guide.md\",\n444:         \"references/opencode/shell/quality_standards.md\",\n445:         \"references/opencode/shell/quick_reference.md\"\n446:     ],\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: ### Surface-aware loading (route-time)\n451: \n452: The router does NOT load the whole matched-intent union. After surface detection (§1, `stack_detection.md`), a route loads:\n453: \n454: - the always-loaded `DEFAULT_RESOURCE` preamble (stack/phase detection, the router, the universal quality baseline), plus\n455: - the surface-agnostic `references/universal/*` tier, plus\n456: - only the **detected surface's** slice (`references/<surface>/*`) for the matched intents, plus\n457: - the Motion.dev overlay (`references/motion_dev/*`) when a `MOTION_DEV` intent fires.\n458: \n459: It does not load the other surface's resources, and it defers `assets/*` (checklists, recipes, templates) to on-demand rather than the first slice. Within OpenCode it slices once more by the **detected language** (§1 sub-detection): a TypeScript task loads `references/opencode/typescript/*` plus the language-agnostic `references/opencode/shared/*`, not the Python, shell, config, or JavaScript folders. Webflow has no language sub-slice — a frontend task legitimately spans CSS, HTML, and JavaScript together. A task that genuinely spans both surfaces (mixed `.opencode/` and Webflow markers) keeps both surface slices; an `UNKNOWN` surface falls back to the preamble plus the universal tier and the Motion overlay only. This is what stops a routine single-surface task from pulling the full cross-surface set. The deterministic router-replay enforces the same rule, so the benchmark measures it.\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"This is the single machine-readable projection of the prose Intent Model (§2) and the per-surface maps (§4 Webflow, §5 Motion.dev, §6 OpenCode). The prose sections above are the human-facing contract; this block is the byte-for-byte source a deterministic router-replay parses. Keep the two in sync: when a map row changes above, update the matching `RESOURCE_MAP` entry here.\n\nA drift guard (`.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`) keeps this block honest: it fails if any path here is missing on disk, if any routable `references/`/`assets/` doc stops being covered, or if an explicit full path named in the prose maps is absent here. Run it standalone with `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` from `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts`.\n\nThis projection is intentionally lossy in two documented ways the flat dictionary cannot express, both enforced by the prose contract and the surface-detection pseudocode in `SKILL.md` §2:\n\n- **No phase boosts.** The `+5` unambiguous-phase boost from the §2 scoring algorithm is not represented; every keyword carries unit weight here.\n- **No doc-only anti-signals.** The `sk-code -2 / sk-doc +3` anti-signals (§2) that route prose-only edits away from this skill are a pre-filter the flat model does not carry.\n\n```python\n# Always-loaded routing preamble: every code task detects stack, detects phase,\n# consults the router, and applies the universal quality baseline before any\n# surface-specific resource. These are loaded on every route.\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = [\n    \"references/stack_detection.md\",\n    \"references/phase_detection.md\",\n    \"references/smart_routing.md\",\n    \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","time":{"start":1780372681791,"end":1780372681804}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_011301244ef57a47016a1e54c9b4888191a99f12b72ae3f7a4"}},"id":"prt_e867b343c001rGggt716HJ6Fzv","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b09f1001Dg9IzKyfXDAokd"}}
