{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372712684,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mSyTNYaFPYr6xcMKMSzDDASF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md","offset":1,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify sk-code routes vanilla-JS / animation-library prompts to the WEBFLOW surface and loads the webflow/* reference and asset trees.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies that sk-code's smart router correctly identifies WEBFLOW as the active code surface when the prompt references vanilla-JS animation libraries (motion.dev, GSAP, Lenis, HLS, Swiper, FilePond) or marker file paths (`src/2_javascript/`, `*.webflow.js`, `wrangler.toml`).\n11: \n12: WEBFLOW is the frontend HTML/CSS/JS surface for Webflow / vanilla-animation projects. When detected, sk-code MUST load `references/webflow/*` and `assets/webflow/*` and SHOULD NOT load any `references/opencode/*` resources.\n13: \n14: Detection markers are defined verbatim in `references/stack_detection.md:30-37`.\n15: \n16: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n17: \n18: **Realistic user request**: A frontend developer working on a Webflow site asks the AI to add smooth-scroll behavior using the Lenis library, gated behind an IntersectionObserver so it only initializes once the user scrolls into the hero section.\n19: \n20: **Exact prompt**:\n21: ```\n22: Add Lenis smooth-scroll to src/2_javascript/scroll.js, gated by IntersectionObserver when the hero becomes visible.\n23: ```\n24: \n25: **Expected detection**:\n26: - Surface: `WEBFLOW`\n27: - Triggering markers: `src/2_javascript/` (path marker) AND `Lenis` (library marker) → either alone is sufficient per `code_surface_detection.md:30-37`.\n28: \n29: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n30: - `references/stack_detection.md` (always loaded for router decision)\n31: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n32: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n33: - `references/phase_detection.md`\n34: - `references/universal/code_quality_standards.md`\n35: - `references/webflow/implementation/webflow_patterns.md`\n36: - `references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md`\n37: - `references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md`\n38: - `references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md`\n39: - `references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md`\n40: - `references/webflow/css/style_guide.md`\n41: - `references/webflow/shared/cross_language_rules.md`\n42: \n43: **Expected assets loaded**:\n44: - `assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md`\n45: - `assets/webflow/patterns/interaction_gate_patterns.js` (when intent is implementation gating)\n46: \n47: **Expected NOT loaded**: any `references/opencode/*` or `assets/opencode/*` (would indicate misrouting).\n48: \n49: **Expected agent dispatch**: `@code` (LEAF) for the actual edit, dispatched ONLY by `@orchestrate`. If the user prompt is invoked directly without orchestration, the AI may apply the change inline using sk-code guidance without dispatching @code.\n50: \n51: **Desired user-visible outcome**: The AI applies the edit to `src/2_javascript/scroll.js`, citing webflow-specific patterns (IntersectionObserver gate from `assets/webflow/patterns/interaction_gate_patterns.js`) and confirming the modification with a Lenis initializer + observer fence.\n52: \n53: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n54: \n55: ### Preconditions\n56: \n57: 1. `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` is at HEAD-of-main.\n58: 2. `references/stack_detection.md:30-37` contains the WEBFLOW marker block (verify with `head -40 .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/stack_detection.md`).\n59: 3. Sandbox: create `/tmp/skc-SD001-sandbox/src/2_javascript/scroll.js` with placeholder content (the AI doesn't need to actually write — we're testing routing).\n60: 4. Skill advisor binary callable: `python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --help` exits 0.\n61: \n62: ### Exact Command Sequence\n63: \n64: 1. **Skill advisor probe**:\n65:    ```\n66:    bash: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py \"Add Lenis smooth-scroll to src/2_javascript/scroll.js, gated by IntersectionObserver when the hero becomes visible.\" --threshold 0.8 > /tmp/skc-SD001-advisor.txt\n67:    ```\n68: 2. **Verify advisor result**: top-1 == `sk-code`, score ≥ 0.80.\n69: 3. **Invoke sk-code** in the orchestrator runtime by feeding the same prompt.\n70: 4. **Capture sk-code output**: which surface did it report? Which references did it list as loaded?\n\n(Showing lines 1-70 of 116. Use offset=71 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify sk-code routes vanilla-JS / animation-library prompts to the WEBFLOW surface and loads the webflow/* reference and asset trees.\"\n---\n\n# SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies that sk-code's smart router correctly identifies WEBFLOW as the active code surface when the prompt references vanilla-JS animation libraries (motion.dev, GSAP, Lenis, HLS, Swiper, FilePond) or marker file paths (`src/2_javascript/`, `*.webflow.js`, `wrangler.toml`).\n\nWEBFLOW is the frontend HTML/CSS/JS surface for Webflow / vanilla-animation projects. When detected, sk-code MUST load `references/webflow/*` and `assets/webflow/*` and SHOULD NOT load any `references/opencode/*` resources.\n\nDetection markers are defined verbatim in `references/stack_detection.md:30-37`.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: A frontend developer working on a Webflow site asks the AI to add smooth-scroll behavior using the Lenis library, gated behind an IntersectionObserver so it only initializes once the user scrolls into the hero section.\n\n**Exact prompt**:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md","time":{"start":1780372712659,"end":1780372712683}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_045946de28b8b2bb016a1e54e89e5c8191a7765a8b6dfd4dbc"}},"id":"prt_e867bacc4001NAmLtBzJNKh52A","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b5ede00124xxzuzxzxnr0L"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372712686,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_57EbWQlIQJvfgXlJBLs40M2A","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/018-webflow-plus-motion-dev.md","offset":1,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/018-webflow-plus-motion-dev.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"CS-001: WEBFLOW Plus Motion.dev Peer References\"\n3: description: \"Verify WEBFLOW animation work also loads cross-stack motion_dev references and assets when the user request uses Motion.dev APIs.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # CS-001: WEBFLOW Plus Motion.dev Peer References\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies the primary cross-stack route: a Webflow frontend request still detects `WEBFLOW`, then loads `motion_dev/` as a peer resource category for Motion.dev API details. The AI must not treat `motion_dev/` as a third surface and must not skip Webflow implementation and verification guidance.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user prompt**:\n17: ```text\n18: For a Webflow hero in src/2_javascript/hero.js, show the pinned Motion CDN pattern and in-view animation snippet.\n19: ```\n20: \n21: **Expected detection markers** (verbatim from `references/stack_detection.md`):\n22: ```bash\n23: # 2. WEBFLOW\n24: [ -d \"src/2_javascript\" ]\n25: ls *.webflow.js 2>/dev/null | head -1\n26: grep -lq \"Webflow\\.push\\|--vw-\" src/**/*.{js,css,html} 2>/dev/null\n27: grep -lqE \"window\\.Motion|window\\.gsap|gsap\\.(to|from|set|timeline|registerPlugin)|new Lenis|new Hls|new Swiper|FilePond\" \\\n28:   src/**/*.{js,mjs,ts,html} *.{js,mjs,ts,html} 2>/dev/null\n29: [ -f \"wrangler.toml\" ]\n30: ```\n31: \n32: **Expected surface**: `WEBFLOW`\n33: \n34: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n35: - `references/stack_detection.md`\n36: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n37: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n38: - `references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md`\n39: - `references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md`\n40: - `references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md`\n41: - `references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md`\n42: - `references/motion_dev/quick_start.md`\n43: - `references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md`\n44: - `references/motion_dev/scroll_and_gestures.md`\n45: - `references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md`\n46: \n47: **Expected assets loaded**:\n48: - `assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md`\n49: - `assets/webflow/checklists/verification_checklist.md`\n50: - `assets/motion_dev/install_card.md`\n51: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js`\n52: - `assets/motion_dev/snippets/cdn_bootstrap.js`\n53: \n54: **Expected agent dispatch**: none for this read-only routing-analysis harness. If the same prompt were implementation work, `@code` could be dispatched by an orchestrator, but this scenario forbids dispatch.\n55: \n56: **Pass/fail criteria with binary grading**:\n57: - **PASS** iff surface is `WEBFLOW`, at least one `references/webflow/implementation/*` path loads, `references/motion_dev/quick_start.md` and `assets/motion_dev/snippets/in_view_reveal.js` load, and `agent_dispatched` is `none`.\n58: - **FAIL** iff surface is not `WEBFLOW`, Motion.dev peer references are omitted, or any agent is dispatched.\n59: \n60: **Failure triage**:\n61: 1. If surface is not `WEBFLOW`, verify the prompt includes `src/2_javascript/` and Webflow terms.\n62: 2. If Motion.dev paths are missing, inspect `references/smart_routing.md` Section 3.\n63: 3. If an agent was dispatched, verify the universal prompt says analyze only and \"DO NOT dispatch any agent.\"\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n68: \n69: Run this scenario through the Phase 005 universal prompt using `SCENARIO_ID=CS-001`. Capture the runtime YAML result and raw transcript.\n70: \n71: Expected result files:\n72: - `/tmp/skc-CS-001-<cli>.txt`\n73: - `<spec-folder><cli>.yaml`\n74: \n75: ---\n\n(Showing lines 1-75 of 93. Use offset=76 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"CS-001: WEBFLOW Plus Motion.dev Peer References\"\ndescription: \"Verify WEBFLOW animation work also loads cross-stack motion_dev references and assets when the user request uses Motion.dev APIs.\"\n---\n\n# CS-001: WEBFLOW Plus Motion.dev Peer References\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies the primary cross-stack route: a Webflow frontend request still detects `WEBFLOW`, then loads `motion_dev/` as a peer resource category for Motion.dev API details. The AI must not treat `motion_dev/` as a third surface and must not skip Webflow implementation and verification guidance.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user prompt**:\n```text\nFor a Webflow hero in src/2_javascript/hero.js, show the pinned Motion CDN pattern and in-view animation snippet.\n```\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/018-webflow-plus-motion-dev.md","time":{"start":1780372712669,"end":1780372712685}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_045946de28b8b2bb016a1e54e89e6c81919e0fc6d732f8f0cc"}},"id":"prt_e867bacd6001VLMNR4X0Z0EtRJ","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b5ede00124xxzuzxzxnr0L"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372712694,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sZStX6Ed3vsgHCRwi1Jv5o97","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","offset":1,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n11: \n12: Sub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**:\n19: ```\n20: Refactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: **Expected detection**:\n24: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n25: - Sub-language: `TYPESCRIPT` (target file `.ts`)\n26: \n27: **Expected references loaded** (must be EXACTLY this set, no more, no less from the language tier):\n28: - `references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md`\n31: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n32: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n33: \n34: **Expected assets loaded**:\n35: - `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`\n36: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n37: \n38: **Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{python,shell,config}/*`, any of `assets/opencode/checklists/{python,shell,config}_checklist.md`.\n39: \n40: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n41: \n42: ### Preconditions\n43: \n44: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`\n45: 2. TypeScript sub-language reference set intact: `bash: ls .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/typescript/ | sort` returns exactly `quality_standards.md style_guide.md quick_reference.md` (in some sort order).\n46: \n47: ### Exact Command Sequence\n48: \n49: 1. **Invoke sk-code** with the prompt.\n50: 2. **Capture loaded refs** to `/tmp/skc-LS001-loaded-refs.txt`.\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 75. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n\nSub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nRefactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","time":{"start":1780372712688,"end":1780372712693}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_045946de28b8b2bb016a1e54e89e748191b72e79a19de00d59"}},"id":"prt_e867bacdf001HntRjQ9GNki0zf","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b5ede00124xxzuzxzxnr0L"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372712707,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QihSmagQktaU3VUlYEan7mHy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","offset":1,"limit":95},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\n3: description: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n6:   - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n7:   - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n8: ---\n9: \n10: # sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n11: \n12: > Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n17: \n18: The deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n19: \n20: Two trace modes score the same playbook corpus:\n21: \n22: - **router** is deterministic and offline. It replays the machine-readable router in `sk-code/references/smart_routing.md`. This is the CI gate.\n23: - **live** dispatches each scenario through `cli-opencode` to a real model and grades the model's stated routing plus observed activation. This is the operator default for a true routing verdict.\n24: \n25: ### Key Statistics\n26: \n27: | Metric | Value |\n28: |---|---|\n29: | Corpus | sk-code `manual_testing_playbook` (24 scenarios: 15 routing, 2 advisor, 7 browser) |\n30: | Trace modes | router (deterministic CI gate), live (real dispatch) |\n31: | Latest router verdict | FAIL, aggregate 40 |\n32: | Latest live verdict | CONDITIONAL, aggregate 71 |\n33: | D4 usefulness (approximate) | about 49 |\n34: \n35: ### How This Compares\n36: \n37: | Tool | Checks | Use When |\n38: |---|---|---|\n39: | This benchmark | Whether the skill is routed, discovered, and useful in practice | Measuring real routing quality |\n40: | `validate.sh` | Document shape and required sections | Checking spec-folder structure |\n41: | `manual_testing_playbook` | Described behavior per scenario | Authoring or hand-running scenarios |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. QUICK START\n46: \n47: Run from the repository root.\n48: \n49: Router mode (deterministic, no network):\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n53:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n54:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/router-final \\\n55:   --trace-mode=router\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Live mode (dispatches through cli-opencode, needs a configured provider):\n59: \n60: ```bash\n61: SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL=openai/gpt-5.5-fast SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high \\\n62: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n63:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n64:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live-final \\\n65:   --trace-mode=live --advisor-mode=python \\\n66:   --scenarios=SD-001,LS-001,CS-001,RD-002,MR-001\n67: ```\n68: \n69: Expected result: a `verdict=` line on stdout plus `skill-benchmark-report.json` and `skill-benchmark-report.md` in the outputs dir.\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. STRUCTURE\n74: \n75: ```text\n76: benchmark/\n77: +-- router-final/      # Current deterministic run (router mode)\n78: +-- live-final/        # Current live run (cli-opencode) + d4-ablation.json\n79: +-- baseline/          # Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, do not regenerate\n80: +-- after/ full/ live/ # Earlier development runs, superseded by the -final pair\n81: `-- fixtures/sk-code/   # Legacy synthetic fixtures, superseded by the playbook corpus\n82: ```\n83: \n84: | Path | Purpose |\n85: |---|---|\n86: | `router-final/` | Latest router-mode report (real-gold scoring, the CI gate) |\n87: | `live-final/` | Latest live-mode report plus `d4-ablation.json` (skill-on vs skill-off usefulness) |\n88: | `baseline/` | First sk-code run, kept as a before-snapshot, not reproducible |\n89: | `fixtures/sk-code/` | Two legacy fixtures, no longer the default corpus |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 4. READING THE REPORTS\n94: \n95: Each run writes a matched pair:\n\n(Showing lines 1-95 of 132. Use offset=96 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\ndescription: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n  - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n  - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n---\n\n# sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n\n> Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n\nTwo trace modes score the same playbook corpus:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","time":{"start":1780372712696,"end":1780372712707}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_045946de28b8b2bb016a1e54e89e7c819180b71e233d856a05"}},"id":"prt_e867bacf2001dxzIL0sLtfjvd6","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b5ede00124xxzuzxzxnr0L"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372712709,"sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jx5vsuH7UPuRG6GisQhRzEFm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/load-playbook-scenarios.cjs","offset":220,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/load-playbook-scenarios.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n220:         source: { featureFile: path.relative(playbookDir, full), shape: 'sk-doc' },\n221:         parseWarnings: prompt ? [] : ['missing-exact-prompt'],\n222:       });\n223:     }\n224:   }\n225:   return out;\n226: }\n227: \n228: /**\n229:  * @returns {{ scenarios: Array, shape: 'sk-code'|'sk-doc'|'none', warnings: string[] }}\n230:  */\n231: function loadPlaybookScenarios({ skillRoot, playbookDir } = {}) {\n232:   const dir = playbookDir || path.join(skillRoot, 'manual_testing_playbook');\n233:   const warnings = [];\n234:   if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n235:     return { scenarios: [], shape: 'none', warnings: [`no playbook at ${dir}`] };\n236:   }\n237:   const rootPath = path.join(dir, 'manual_testing_playbook.md');\n238:   const rootText = readFileSafe(rootPath);\n239:   const index = rootText ? parseRootIndex(rootText) : [];\n240:   const rootMap = rootText ? parseRootScenarioTables(rootText) : {};\n241: \n242:   if (index.length > 0) {\n243:     const scenarios = [];\n244:     for (const row of index) {\n245:       const abs = path.join(dir, row.featureFile);\n246:       const parsed = parseFeatureFile(abs, row.scenarioId, row.categoryLabel, row.critical, rootMap[row.scenarioId]);\n247:       if (parsed) {\n248:         if (parsed.parseWarnings.length) warnings.push(`${row.scenarioId}: ${parsed.parseWarnings.join(',')}`);\n249:         scenarios.push(parsed);\n250:       } else {\n251:         warnings.push(`${row.scenarioId}: feature file unreadable (${row.featureFile})`);\n252:       }\n253:     }\n254:     return { scenarios, shape: 'sk-code', warnings };\n255:   }\n256: \n257:   // No root index table -> sk-doc YAML-frontmatter shape.\n258:   const scenarios = loadYamlFrontmatterScenarios(dir);\n259:   return { scenarios, shape: scenarios.length ? 'sk-doc' : 'none', warnings };\n260: }\n261: \n262: module.exports = { loadPlaybookScenarios, classifyKind, extractPaths, parseRootIndex };\n263: \n264: if (require.main === module) {\n265:   const args = require('./_args.cjs').parse(process.argv.slice(2));\n266:   const skillRoot = args.skill && (args.skill.includes('/') || args.skill.startsWith('.'))\n267:     ? path.resolve(args.skill)\n268:     : path.join(path.resolve(__dirname, '..', '..', '..'), args.skill || '');\n269:   const res = loadPlaybookScenarios({ skillRoot, playbookDir: args['playbook-dir'] });\n270:   process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(res, null, 2) + '\\n');\n271: }\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        source: { featureFile: path.relative(playbookDir, full), shape: 'sk-doc' },\n        parseWarnings: prompt ? [] : ['missing-exact-prompt'],\n      });\n    }\n  }\n  return out;\n}\n\n/**\n * @returns {{ scenarios: Array, shape: 'sk-code'|'sk-doc'|'none', warnings: string[] }}\n */\nfunction loadPlaybookScenarios({ skillRoot, playbookDir } = {}) {\n  const dir = playbookDir || path.join(skillRoot, 'manual_testing_playbook');\n  const warnings = [];\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    return { scenarios: [], shape: 'none', warnings: [`no playbook at ${dir}`] };\n  }\n  const rootPath = path.join(dir, 'manual_testing_playbook.md');\n  const rootText = readFileSafe(rootPath);\n  const index = rootText ? parseRootIndex(rootText) : [];","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/load-playbook-scenarios.cjs","time":{"start":1780372712704,"end":1780372712709}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_045946de28b8b2bb016a1e54e89e848191bde842f24c5b4f34"}},"id":"prt_e867bacf90017rXzy0gPBdu49x","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867b5ede00124xxzuzxzxnr0L"}}
