ared/* refs loaded; 0 typescript/shell/config refs.\n52: \n53: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n54: \n55: - **PASS** iff: 3 python/* refs + 2 shared/* refs loaded AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n56: - **FAIL** iff: any typescript/shell/config ref leaks, OR fewer than 3 python/* refs loaded.\n57: \n58: ### Failure Triage\n59: \n60: 1. If a typescript/* ref leaks: the extension detector is mis-firing on the `.py` extension.\n61: 2. If python signals not detected: verify `argparse`, `pytest`, `def `, docstring patterns in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n\n(Showing lines 20-64 of 74. Use offset=65 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Update the skill_advisor.py argparse block at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py to add a --json-output flag that emits results as JSON.\n```\n\n**Expected detection**:\n- Surface: `OPENCODE`\n- Sub-language: `PYTHON` (target file `.py`, also Python-specific signal: `argparse`)\n\n**Expected references loaded**:\n- `references/opencode/python/style_guide.md`\n- `references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md`\n- `references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md`\n- `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n- `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n\n**Expected assets loaded**:\n- `assets/opencode/checklists/python_checklist.md`\n- `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n\n**Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{typescript,shell,config}/*`.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md","time":{"start":1780372750606,"end":1780372750609}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_005a06eaf3dc34ef016a1e550e858481918de4e4789b514cdf"}},"id":"prt_e867c410c001LJoj8W9rPJOWZl","sessionID":"ses_17985835dffe8as3Ygnwtbh8Aj","messageID":"msg_e867c2173001oujn8yZlCSecgN"}}
